Subject: [PATCH] feat(operations): ensure dashboard reflects live reservation
 data

Phase 2A re-implementation, Milestone 5 - final milestone.

- app/operations/page.tsx: added export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"
  (plus a short explanatory comment) directly above OperationsPage.
  No other change to this file, and no change to lib/operations.ts or
  any of the 4 operations components.

Necessary because lib/operations.ts already reads the shared bookings
array correctly -- the only gap was the risk of Next.js statically
optimizing this route and never re-reading it.

Verified with npx tsc --noEmit and npm run lint (both clean).
npm run build fails only on 3 Google Fonts fetches (Inter, Fraunces,
IBM Plex Mono), confirmed via curl to be a pre-existing sandbox
network restriction (fonts.googleapis.com returns
x-deny-reason: host_not_allowed), unrelated to this or any prior
Phase 2A change.

This completes Phase 2A (re-implementation): customer booking creates
a reservation record, availability uses inventory + reservations,
confirmation uses reference lookup, and the operations dashboard
reflects new reservations -- with no database, authentication, API
routes, payments, or admin systems introduced.
